HEADWORD: Chiliad
<hw>Chil"i*ad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chilia`s</grk>, <grk>chiliado`s</grk>, fr. <grk>chi`lioi</grk> a
thousand.]</ety> <def>A thousand; the aggregate of a thousand things;
especially, a period of a thousand years.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The world, then in the seventh <qex>chiliad</qex>, will be assumed
up unto God.</q> <rj><qau>Sir. T. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chiliagon</ent>⟦br⟧
